		<h2>IVF Protocols</h2>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Long Lupron (Agonist):</strong> Suppression starts before stimulation</li>
			<li><strong>Antagonist:</strong> More common; shorter cycle, fewer injections</li>
			<li><strong>Mini/Micro IVF:</strong> Lower dose medications, fewer eggs, lower cost</li>
			<li><strong>Natural Cycle IVF:</strong> No or minimal medications; single egg</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Risks</h2>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>OHSS:</strong> 1-5% moderate-severe; requires monitoring</li>
			<li><strong>Multiple pregnancy:</strong> 2-3% with single embryo transfer</li>
			<li><strong>Ectopic pregnancy:</strong> 2-5%</li>
			<li><strong>Cycle cancellation:</strong> Poor response or over-response</li>
			<li><strong>Egg retrieval risks:</strong> Bleeding, infection (rare)</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Finding a Clinic</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Check SART.org for clinic success rates</li>
			<li>Compare rates for your age group and diagnosis</li>
			<li>Consider location, cost, and patient reviews</li>
			<li>Ask about their specific protocols and philosophy</li>
		</ul>

